<br>
There have been several nice posts with good coments folowing, but not too many.<br>
<br>
Now to add my own worthless comments...<br>
<br>
On the point system:<br>
<br>
I like the point system because it encourages PVP,  For those that know me this is a high priority for me.   Anything that encourages PVP ( and team play ) is a good thing.<br>
<br>
Is the point system fair:<br>
<br>
Well no not.   Why?  Well for the simple fact that the point system was developed AFTER people rolled up thier charecters and started playing.  If I had wanted points I would have prolly rolled up the ubiquitious 1/2ling druid as well.<br>
<br>
Does it favor one or two classes over others:<br>
<br>
Ill let the point system speak for all of us there.  Eq has always favored Druids and Wizards in PVP.  The team with those two classes will dominate this server in the long run.  I know thats my opinion and not too popular but the game dynamics point to this conclusion.  In my modest experience on Vallon, Druids and Wizards were always a big factor in making a guild viable and competitive in PVP.<br>
<br>
So why are you playing a Mage?<br>
<br>
Well I wanted to play this class, in my last go round with eq, before I quit eq for some other game.<br>
